<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1151,1285]" pageId="1" pageNumber="305">
<taxonomicName box="[151,237,1153,1176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Joruma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="305" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,237,1153,1176]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="305">Joruma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily distinguished from other genera of subfamily 
<taxonomicName box="[969,1135,1151,1176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="305" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Typhlocybinae">Typhlocybinae</taxonomicName>
mainly by the following combination of characteristics: eyes large; ocelli present and conspicuous; forewings without appendix, r-m inconspicuous; hind wings with anal margin serrated, submarginal vein not extending beyond MP, vein R reduced; male anal hooks present.
</paragraph>
